metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Tale Of A Cruel World
metadata.editComments:
We're in the finale now, the main juice of the piece, the main melodic motif called back to all throughout the soundtrack, the chorus. This is the part I struggled notating the most, with the three-part melody that I'm obviously too broke to be able to replicate. (Not like I even did any work, shoutout to StormGem on Musescore for the original transcription). As such, the melody is probably WAY off and the "chords" are inaccurate, so someone with better ears feel free to fix it.

But enough of that, what makes it special? Well, we've shifted for a more "classical prelude" sort of vibe, perfect for a calm intro piece to the story of a crapsaccharine apocalypse world ruled by a depressed tyrant. But harmonically? uh, there's a #viio7/V chord, that's always really *juicy* and emotional, and there's a D (or Ebb) over a Dbmaj7 chord in Bar 13, but that's it. That's okay, though, you don't *always* need impossibly complex jazz chords and advanced music theory to get your point across.
